<section id="faq" class="faq-section">
        <div class="container">
          <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
          <div class="faq-list">
            <details class="faq-item">
              <summary class="faq-question">How to write a resume?</summary>
              <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>Start with your contact details, then add a short career objective or summary. Follow with your education, work experience, skills, and projects in reverse-chronological order. Use clear section headings, bullet points, and action verbs, and tailor the content to the job you're applying for so it passes ATS screening.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
            <details class="faq-item">
              <summary class="faq-question">How to make a resume?</summary>
              <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>Choose an ATS-friendly resume template, fill in your personal details, education, skills, and experience, and keep the formatting simple with standard fonts and clear headings. You can use a free resume builder like ResumeWithCareer to generate a polished resume in minutes without any design skills.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
            <details class="faq-item">
              <summary class="faq-question">What is a CV vs resume?</summary>
              <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>A resume is a concise 1-2 page document summarizing your skills, experience, and education for a specific job application. A CV (Curriculum Vitae) is a longer, more detailed document covering your entire academic and professional history, commonly used for academic, research, or international job applications.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
            <details class="faq-item">
              <summary class="faq-question">How to add resume to LinkedIn?</summary>
              <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>Log in to LinkedIn, go to your profile, click "Add profile section" or the "Open to" button, and select "Media" under the featured section to upload your resume as a PDF or DOC file. You can also attach your resume directly when applying to jobs through LinkedIn's Easy Apply feature.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
